universe-collect: wide token-pool collector for seed-pool expansion

Adds `npm run universe:collect` — pulls a wide pool of ACTIVE Solana tokens
(not just pumped ones) and dumps their swap history to cache/universe.json
in the same shape as cache/pump.json. Drop-in input for whales:extract.

The H8 rotation pipeline currently surfaces 11 MEMECOIN-OP candidates from
100 seeds derived from 8 cached tokens. Scaling tokens by 10x should give
us ~10x more anchor whales and ~10x more rotation candidates, growing the
operator watchlist organically.

Why a separate command from seed:pump:
- seed:pump targets pumped tokens specifically and writes to watchlist
- collect-universe gathers RAW active-token data without pump filter or DB
  writes — purely for downstream offline use (extract-whales -> rotation)

CLI knobs: UNIV_TARGET_TOKENS / UNIV_PAGES / UNIV_MIN_LIQ / UNIV_MIN_VOL /
UNIV_MIN_AGE_HOURS / UNIV_MAX_AGE_DAYS / UNIV_OUT / UNIV_DRY_RUN.

Defaults: 100 tokens * 5 pages = 50k credits per run (fits in daily budget).
